<subSubSection id="C33F0EE1EF7D7B63FF24FAF4759FD491" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9A5D6AEF7D7B63FF24FAF4759FD491" blockId="1.[151,1437,1231,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FF24FAF47088D405" bold="true" box="[199,464,1339,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2526E9EF7D7B63FC5BFAF4753AD405" box="[952,1122,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FC5BFAF4753AD405" box="[952,1122,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Montanocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2526E9EF7D7B63FAD7FAF3701DD42A" authority="Barkalov, 2005" authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milkoi">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FAD7FAF374C4D405" box="[1332,1436,1339,1366]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">C. milkoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB4209BEF7D7B63FF74FA90701DD42A" author="Barkalov, A. V." box="[151,325,1375,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" pagination="669 - 676" refId="ref10464" refString="Barkalov, A. V. (2005) New species of the genus Cheilosia Mg. (Diptera, Syrphidae) from Middle Asia. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 84 (3), 669 - 676. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2005">Barkalov, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2526E9EF7D7B63FEB3FAAF7362D429" authority="Peck, 1969" authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1969" box="[336,570,1375,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zlotini">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FEB3FAAF70EFD429" box="[336,439,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">C. zlotini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB4209BEF7D7B63FE5DFA907362D429" author="Peck, L. V." box="[446,570,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" pagination="201 - 210" refId="ref11133" refString="Peck, L. V. (1969) Some new species of hover-flies (Diptera, Syrphidae) from Tian-Shan. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 48 (1), 201 - 210. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1969">Peck, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2526E9EF7D7B63FD92FAAF723ED429" authority="Peck, 1969" authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1969" box="[625,870,1375,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vtorovi">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FD92FAAF7387D429" box="[625,735,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">C. vtorovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB4209BEF7D7B63FD05FA90723ED429" author="Peck, L. V." box="[742,870,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" pagination="201 - 210" refId="ref11133" refString="Peck, L. V. (1969) Some new species of hover-flies (Diptera, Syrphidae) from Tian-Shan. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 48 (1), 201 - 210. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1969">Peck, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. From all of these species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2526E9EF7D7B63FB76FAAF7464D429" authority="Barkalov, 2020" authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2020" box="[1173,1340,1375,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teneripilosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FB76FAAF7464D429" box="[1173,1340,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">C. teneripilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FAA0FA9074C4D429" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2623C03EF7D7B63FAA0FA9074C4D429" box="[1347,1436,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs by the following set of characters: eyes with long black hairs, legs of male completely black, abdomen predominantly with light hairs, superior lobe of hypandrium with very small left process (
<figureCitation id="131E41EFEF7D7B63FB82FA6875E2D491" box="[1121,1210,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,315,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,309,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cheilosia teneripilosa sp. nov. A: head of male, lateral view. B: head of female, dorsal view. C: pedicel and postpedicel of male, lateral view. D: superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. E: aedeagus with apodeme. F: surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view; l. p., left process of superior lobe; r. p., right process of superior lobe. Scale bar in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413751/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33F0EE1EF7D7B61FF24FA0470DDD0FD" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="246" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9A5D6AEF7D7B60FF24FA0472C6D04D" blockId="1.[151,1437,1231,2020]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,150,285]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="245" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FF24FA0470A9D4B5" bold="true" box="[199,497,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">
Description. MALE. 
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FE21FA0470A9D4B5" bold="true" box="[450,497,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Size</emphasis>
</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity id="4CDDF08FEF7D7B63FD72FA0473A0D4B6" box="[657,760,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" unit="mm" value="12.3">12.3 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="4CDDF08FEF7D7B63FC73FA0472BAD4B6" box="[912,994,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="244" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FC0EFA047573D4B6" bold="true" box="[1005,1067,1483,1510]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131E41EFEF7D7B63FBD8FA0475CDD4B5" box="[1083,1173,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,315,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,309,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cheilosia teneripilosa sp. nov. A: head of male, lateral view. B: head of female, dorsal view. C: pedicel and postpedicel of male, lateral view. D: superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. E: aedeagus with apodeme. F: surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view; l. p., left process of superior lobe; r. p., right process of superior lobe. Scale bar in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413751/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Face broad, distinctly broadened ventrally, black, shiny with fine grey dusting denser under antennae base, ventrally with narrow strip of microtrichia, without distinct hairs, shiny stripe without dusting laterally. Central knob distinct but not prominent, shiny, without dusting. Eye-margin broad, black, shiny, with fine brownish dusting and long black hairs. Genae very high, covered with grey dusting and long black hairs, some yellow hairs posteriorly. Frons distinctly swollen, broad, shiny, covered with long black hairs, frontal angle more than 100°. Lunula dark-brown almost black; anten- nal pits distinctly separated.Antennae black, scapus and pedicel with grey dusting, postpedicel comparatively small, rounded, black with brownish postero-ventral angle, covered with brown dusting (
<figureCitation id="131E41EFEF7D7B63FBDEF90875CCD7B1" box="[1085,1172,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,315,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,309,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cheilosia teneripilosa sp. nov. A: head of male, lateral view. B: head of female, dorsal view. C: pedicel and postpedicel of male, lateral view. D: superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. E: aedeagus with apodeme. F: surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view; l. p., left process of superior lobe; r. p., right process of superior lobe. Scale bar in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413751/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); arista long, gradually tapering, bare, black. Eyes covered with long dense black hairs, eye contiguity approximately equal to frons length without lunula. Vertex swollen, covered with grey dusting and long black hairs, ocellar triangle equilateral. Occiput covered with long black and yellow hairs. 
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7D7B63FD97F8FC7388D61E" bold="true" box="[628,720,1843,1870]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum black with fine grey dusting and black hairs. Scutum black with fine granulation, and dense long erect fine black hairs with half-length white hairs, some long white hairs near scutellum. Scutellum black, covered with long, fine black and yellow hairs, without any bristles. Pleura black with grey dusting and dense long fine black hairs. Legs black with black long hairs; fore coxa without lateral spur. Wing translucent, with brownish base, completely covered with microtrichia, inner angle between veins M 
<subScript id="17A15F2FEF7D7B63FAD7F8197464D6B4" attach="left" box="[1332,1340,2006,2020]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">1</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17A15F2FEF7D7B63FA60F81A74C5D6B3" attach="left" box="[1411,1437,2005,2019]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="244">4+5</subScript>
acute. Haltere with yellow pedicel and black capitulum. Calypters yellow with white cilia. 
<emphasis id="B9518178EF7E7B60FB76FF59745BD1E1" bold="true" box="[1173,1283,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="245">Abdomen</emphasis>
elongated, in the broadest part distinctly narrower than scutum at the level of wing base; shiny black, tergites II–III with brownish dusting medially, covered with long, dense, erect, mostly light-yellow hairs, black hairs on lateral sides of tergites. Sternites black, matt, with black hairs. Hypopygium as in 
<figureCitation id="131E41EFEF7E7B60FCC2FECC723AD04D" box="[801,866,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,315,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,309,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cheilosia teneripilosa sp. nov. A: head of male, lateral view. B: head of female, dorsal view. C: pedicel and postpedicel of male, lateral view. D: superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. E: aedeagus with apodeme. F: surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view; l. p., left process of superior lobe; r. p., right process of superior lobe. Scale bar in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413751/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="245">Figs 1</figureCitation>
D–F.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5A0DE2EF7E7B60FF74F8837582D6FC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413751" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4413751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413751/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="245" startId="2.[151,250,1868,1892]" targetBox="[165,1424,315,1836]" targetPageId="2">
